Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1} in a #colander{}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Break the mince up with a #spoon{} as it cooks. Stir in the garlic and @Mexican style spice mix{1} and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Lower the heat to medium and stir in the @tomato puree{30%g}, @basmati rice{150%g}, kidney beans and the @water{350%ml}. Stir in @red wine jus paste{1} until it has dissolved. Bring to the boil, then cover the pan with a #lid{} or some #kitchen foil{}.

Leave to cook for ~{15%mins}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam - don't look under the lid!). Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Preheat your #grill{} to high. Once the rice is cooked, remove the lid from the pan and season to taste with salt and pepper. Stir through half the coriander. Sprinkle on the cheese, then pop the pan under grill until the cheese is golden and bubbling, ~{2-3%mins}.

Share the Mexican rice between your #plates{}, top with the remaining coriander and enjoy!

> We love Beef and Rice with Cheesy Topping and this deliciously simple, chef-curated recipe doesn't disappoint. Time to bust out the pots and pans!